<h1>Lara McPherson</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://laramcpherson.com/info">laramcpherson.com/info</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Melbourne

Australia
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Strategist specialising in communications, social impact, digital innovation, authentic engagement. / Student of Progressive Economics.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I explore why we do what we do, and how we can do it better.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
My primary driver in life is to understand things. Once I understand them I'm compelled to try and make them as good as they can be - and for me, good means creating more opportunities for meaningful connections with others and working toward greater economic justice.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Improving the standard of education should be the goal of any developed economy. / "The arts are not a way to make a living. They are a very human way of making life more bearable." - Kurt Vonnegut
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Affluenza by Denniss and Hamilton <<a href="http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/48831.Affluenza>,">http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/48831.Affluenza>,</a> and any writing by George Monbiot <<a href="http://www.theguardian.com/profile/georgemonbiot>">http://www.theguardian.com/profile/georgemonbiot></a> and Umair Haque <<a href="https://medium.com/@umairh>.">https://medium.com/@umairh>.</a> If you want something more optimistic, I love Miranda Darling <<a href="http://www.thegirlwithpearls-miranda.blogspot.com.au/>'s">http://www.thegirlwithpearls-miranda.blogspot.com.au/>'s</a> writing for RUSSH Mag.
</p>

